[parameters: ('qa-000025', 'What is the best way to respond to negative media coverage of IDPs?', 'The best way to respond to negative media coverage of IDPs is to issue a public statement condemning the article and promoting a positive narrative about IDPs, and to engage with media outlets to promote more nuanced and accurate coverage.', '["internally-displaced-persons-coverage", "hate-speech-in-media"]', 'intermediate', 'Failing to respond to negative media coverage, allowing the narrative to go unchallenged.', 'internally-displaced-persons-coverage', 'qa-000026', 'How can I promote a positive narrative about IDPs?', 'You can promote a positive narrative about IDPs by challenging negative stereotypes and hate speech, and promoting a more nuanced and accurate understanding of the community through media outreach, public statements, and community engagement.', '["internally-displaced-persons-coverage", "promoting-a-positive-narrative"]', 'basic', 'Failing to challenge negative stereotypes and hate speech, and allowing the narrative to go unchallenged.', None, 'qa-000027', 'What is the importance of reporting hate speech?', 'Reporting hate speech is essential to holding media outlets accountable and promoting a culture of respect and inclusivity. It can help to prevent the spread of hate speech and promote a more nuanced and accurate understanding of the community.', '["hate-speech-in-media", "reporting-hate-speech"]', 'intermediate', 'Failing to report incidents of hate speech, and allowing the behavior to continue.', 'hate-speech-in-media')]
